ZH: 我已经服用了安眠药，希望能早点入睡。
EN: I have taken a sleeping pill, hoping to sleep early.
ZH: 安眠药不宜长期服用。
EN: Sleeping pills should not be used for a long time.
ZH: 她在睡前喝了杯牛奶和一颗安眠药。
EN: She drank a glass of milk and took a sleeping pill before bed.
ZH: 医生建议我服用安眠药来帮助我入睡。
EN: The doctor suggested that I take sleeping pills to help me sleep.
ZH: 安眠药可以缓解失眠问题。
EN: Sleeping pills can help relieve insomnia problems.
ZH: 请不要将安眠药用于儿童。
EN: Please do not use sleeping pills for children.
ZH: 我不喜欢依赖安眠药来入睡。
EN: I don't like relying on sleeping pills to fall asleep.
ZH: 昨晚我忘记服用安眠药，难以入睡。
EN: I forgot to take my sleeping pills last night and had trouble falling asleep.
ZH: 安眠药会在30分钟内起效。
EN: The sleeping pill will take effect within 30 minutes.
ZH: 如果你无法入睡，可以考虑服用安眠药。
EN: If you can't fall asleep, consider taking a sleeping pill.
ZH: 我宁愿不服用安眠药也不愿忍受失眠。
EN: I'd rather not take a sleeping pill than endure insomnia.
ZH: 他常常靠安眠药来维持健康的睡眠。
EN: He often relies on sleeping pills to maintain a healthy sleep.
ZH: 使用安眠药可能会导致嗜睡和头痛。
EN: Using sleeping pills may cause drowsiness and headache.
ZH: 最好在医生的建议下使用安眠药。
EN: It's best to use sleeping pills under the advice of a doctor.
ZH: 安眠药须使用处方方可购买。
EN: Sleeping pills must be purchased with a prescription.
ZH: 不要将安眠药和酒精一起服用。
EN: Do not take sleeping pills with alcohol.
ZH: 我希望这是最后一次需要服用安眠药。
EN: I hope this is the last time I need to take sleeping pills.
ZH: 她对安眠药有依赖性，需要寻求专业帮助。
EN: She is dependent on sleeping pills and needs professional help.
ZH: 明天一早我会去看医生，咨询更好的安眠药。
EN: I will go see a doctor tomorrow morning to inquire about better sleeping pills.
